item.content:encoded:
State of Florida Annual Open Enrollment for 2012

Important November 7 - November 18, 2011

Open Enrollment takes place each fall to allow eligible employeesexcepting OPS employeesto make changes to their insurance plans for the upcoming year. All changes will be effective the following January and must be done through People First. You can contact them by calling 1-866-663-4735 or visiting their website at peoplefirst.myflorida.com.

State Sponsored Plan Changes Important Dates & Mailings How to Enroll or Make Changes Open Enrollment FAQ Open Enrollment Information Sessions Open Enrollment Session Powerpoint View an Open Enrollment Presentation  

What's new for 2012 Open Enrollment

HMO Options and Changes:

  • AvMed Providers
  • BCBS Providers
  • Aetna Providers
  • HMO Service Areas by County

Health Savings Accounts (HSA) Changes:

  • Contribution Limits for HSAs

Prescription Changes:

  • Medco: State Employees' Prescription Drug Plan

Dental Changes:

  • Dental Plan Rates
 
Enroll or make changes to the following plans during Open Enrollment
Current 2011 State Sponsored Benefits:
  • Health Insurance
  • Basic & Optional Life
  • Flexible Spending Accounts and HSAs
  • Dental
  • Vision
  • Short Term Disability
  • Hospital Income
  • Cancer
Open Enrollment Resources for 2012: State of Florida Information
  • 2012 Enrollment Brochures
  • 2012 Active and Retiree Benefits Guide
  • Open Enrollment Newsletter for 2012
  • State of Florida Mybenefits website
  • Basic Insurance Definitions
  • Health and Dental Cost Estimators
  • Contact an Insurance Company
   

How to Enroll or Make Changes

  • Visit the People First website at peoplefirst.myflorida.com (available 24/7)
  • Speak to a People First representative at 1-866-663-4735 (866-221-0268 TTY users) Monday - Friday between 8:00 a.m. and 6 p.m
  • Complete a paper enrollment and submit to People First directly by mailing or by fax 1-800-422-3128be sure to make a copy for yourself
  You will need your People First user ID and password to access your enrollment account. If you don't have them, contact People First after reviewing the People First password guidelines.  

Need help using People First's website?

Visit hr.ucf.edu/web/benefits/People_First for a PDF that shows you how to enroll on the website. If you need additional instructions, training videos are available to help you.    

Open Enrollment Information Sessions

Human Resources' benefits team will host Open Enrollment Information Sessions to discuss plan changes for 2012. Attending these sessions is voluntary, but strongly recommended; there are often changes could impact your benefits. You can view the session schedule here.
Date Time Location
January 1, 2012 4:00-5:00 PM Student Union, Room 235
January 1, 2012 4:00-5:00 PM Millican Hall, Room 330
January 1, 2012 4:00-5:00 PM Innovative Center, Room 100
   

Important Dates & Mailings

Here's what to expect in the coming year regarding key mailings about changes to Important dates:

September 2012

  • People First will begin mailing your benefits statements to your home
  • People First will be available to provide information and assistancere-establish your password and review your plan information

October 8, 2012

  • Open Enrollment begins at 8:00 a.m. ESTyou may visit the website to enroll or call 1-866-663-4735 (TTY 866-221-0268) so specialists can help you

November 2, 2012

  • Open Enrollment closes at 6:00 p.m. EST

October 8 - November 16, 2012

  • Confirmations will be mailed out to employees who made changes to their enrollments

November 5 - December 16, 2012

  • Corrections to Open Enrollment must be made by 6:00 p.m. ESTcall People First at 1-866-663-4735 (TTY 866-221-0268) to make changes

item.title: HR Liasons
item.dc:creator: jogreybill
item.content:encoded:
Human Resources Information Systems (HRIS)

The HRIS section strives to provide the most up-to-date reference materials and training on PeopleSoft. We currently offer the following UCF Human Resources manuals:
  • 9.0 Employee Self Service User Guide
  • 9.0 PeopleSoft Payroll Glossary
  • 9.0 Running Processes and Reports in PeopleSoft
  • 9.0 Time and Leave Sheet Instructions
  • 9.0 Time and Leave Sheet Quick Reference Guide
  • 9.0 Time Approval Procedure Manual
  • 9.0 Time Processor Procedure Manual
  • 9.0 Faculty/Staff Position File Manual
  • 9.0 OPS Employee File Manual
   

The PeopleSoft Upgrade Project

During the project, HRIS recognized the need for, and developed a focus group to review the delivered functionality of the new system to:
  • Discuss how to better allow use of the system, as delivered
  • Provide recommendations for system enhancements when changes in business practices are not possible due to regulations
The focus group, known as the Human Resources PeopleSoft Advisory Group (HRPAG), is comprised of payroll processors and payroll authorizers from each college/division. If you would like to speak with a representative from HRIS, please call (407) 823-2771 or e-mail hris@ucf.edu.    

HR Liason Toolkit

To improve communication between our department and yours, the HR Liaison Program was designed to assist your department with HR procedures.

Program Overview

  • In Fall 2005, HR created a liaison workshop to guide you through the sometimes complicated HR business processes, as well as details as to why the process is sometimes complicated
  • A toolkit of valuable information, including guides, checklists and resources are provided from all of our offices
  • If you complete the entire session, you are added to the HR Liaison ListServ, an email group that is the first to receive important HR-related announcements and updates

Program Tools

To update your HR Liaison toolkit with the Powerpoint from the latest workshop, click on the links below:
  • Benefits
  • Compensation
  • Employee Relations
  • HR Overview/Introduction
  • Payroll
  • OD & Training
  • Records
  • Recruitment

item.content:encoded: [post-type-search post_type_name="resourcelink" taxonomy="pg_sections" default_search_label="Find a Resource" default_search_text="Search..."]

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value:
The A-Z Index is designed to offer employees a central source to obtain general information related to their employment with the University of Central Florida. Previously, the University compiled much, but not all, of this information into a printed handbook. The University no longer provides printed handbooks of that type, but rather relies upon more expansive on-line resources. The information contained on-line in the A-Z Index web pages supersedes all prior printed handbooks, which are out of date.

Please note this information is general in scope and nothing in this information is intended to create binding contractual commitments between an employee and the University, or to limit the rights of employees or UCF. Employees are encouraged to contact their immediate supervisor or Human Resources should they have any questions regarding the information.
